api_list.name: addAddressToUnsubscribeTable

required_parameters.description: The api key obtained from MailGun.

optional_parameters.name: createdAt
optional_parameters.description: Timestamp of a bounce event.

optional_parameters.name: vars
optional_parameters.description: JSON-encoded dictionary string with arbitrary parameters, e.g. {'gender':'female','age':27}

api_list.name: sendEmail
api_list.description: Sends an email.

required_parameters.name: apiKey
required_parameters.description: The api key obtained from MailGun.

required_parameters.name: mTo
required_parameters.description: Email address of the recipient(s). ('Bob bob@host.com'). You can use commas to separate multiple recipients.

optional_parameters.name: inline
optional_parameters.description: Attachment with inline disposition.

optional_parameters.name: text
optional_parameters.description: Body of the message. (text version).

optional_parameters.name: html
optional_parameters.description: Body of the message. (HTML version).

optional_parameters.name: subject
optional_parameters.description: Message subject.

optional_parameters.name: o:campaign
optional_parameters.description: Id of the campaign the message belongs to. See um-campaign-analytics for details.

optional_parameters.name: o:tracking
optional_parameters.description: Toggles tracking on a per-message basis, see Tracking Messages for details. Pass yes or no.

optional_parameters.name: o:skip-verification
optional_parameters.description: If set to True, the certificate and hostname will not be verified when trying to establish a TLS connection and Mailgun will accept any certificate during delivery.

optional_parameters.name: o:deliverytime
optional_parameters.description: Desired time of delivery. See Date Format. Note: Messages can be scheduled for a maximum of 3 days in the future.

optional_parameters.name: o:tracking-opens
optional_parameters.description: Toggles opens tracking on a per-message basis. Has higher priority than domain-level setting. Pass yes or no.

optional_parameters.name: v:my-var
optional_parameters.description: v: prefix followed by an arbitrary name allows to attach a custom JSON data to the message. See Attaching Data to Messages for more information.

optional_parameters.name: h:X-My-Header
optional_parameters.description: h: prefix followed by an arbitrary value allows to append a custom MIME header to the message (X-My-Header in this case).

optional_parameters.name: o:dkim
optional_parameters.description: Enables/disables DKIM signatures on per-message basis. Pass yes or no.

optional_parameters.name: o:require-tls
optional_parameters.description: This requires the message only be sent over a TLS connection. (True or False)

optional_parameters.name: o:tracking-clicks
optional_parameters.description: Toggles clicks tracking on a per-message basis. Has higher priority than domain-level setting. Pass yes, no or htmlonly.

optional_parameters.name: o:testmode
optional_parameters.description: Enables sending in test mode. Pass yes if needed. See Sending in Test Mode.

optional_parameters.name: cc
optional_parameters.description: Same as 'To' but for Cc.

optional_parameters.name: bcc
optional_parameters.description: Same as 'To' but for Bcc.

optional_parameters.name: o:tag
optional_parameters.description: Tag string.
